    "message_1": "Suppose you have a One-time pad encryption key with a length of 10 and it reads as: 1010110011. Encipher the message \"MATHISFUN\" using the provided key and then decipher the enciphered message to get the original message back. Show all your work.",
    "message_2": "To encipher the message \"MATHISFUN\" using the One-time pad encryption key, we first need to convert the message into binary form. We can use the ASCII values of the characters and then convert them to 8-bit binary representation.\n\nM -> 77  -> 01001101\nA -> 65  -> 01000001\nT -> 84  -> 01010100\nH -> 72  -> 01001000\nI -> 73  -> 01001001\nS -> 83  -> 01010011\nF -> 70  -> 01000110\nU -> 85  -> 01010101\nN -> 78  -> 01001110\n\nNow, we need to break the 10-bit key into 8-bit segments to XOR with the binary representation of the message. Since the key is 10 bits long, we will repeat the key to match the length of the message.\n\nKey: 10101100111010110011101011001110101100111010110011\n\nNow, we XOR the binary message with the key:\n\n01001101 ⊕ 10101100 = 11100001\n01000001 ⊕ 11101011 = 10101010\n01010100 ⊕ 00111010 = 01101110\n01001000 ⊕ 11001110 = 10000110\n01001001 ⊕ 10101100 = 11100101\n01010011 ⊕ 11101011 = 10111000\n01000110 ⊕ 00111010 = 01111100\n01010101 ⊕ 11001110 = 10011011\n01001110 ⊕ 10101100 = 11100010\n\nThe enciphered message in binary is:\n\n11100001 10101010 01101110 10000110 11100101 10111000 01111100 10011011 11100010\n\nNow, let's decipher the enciphered message using the same key:\n\n11100001 ⊕ 10101100 = 01001101\n10101010 ⊕ 11101011 = 01000001\n01101110 ⊕ 00111010 = 01010100\n10000110 ⊕ 11001110 = 01001000\n11100101 ⊕ 10101100 = 01001001\n10111000 ⊕ 11101011 = 01010011\n01111100 ⊕ 00111010 = 01000110\n10011011 ⊕ 11001110 = 01010101\n11100010 ⊕ 10101100 = 01001110\n\nThe deciphered message in binary is:\n\n01001101 01000001 01010100 01001000 01001001 01010011 01000110 01010101 01001110\n\nNow, let's convert the binary back to ASCII characters:\n\n01001101 -> 77  -> M\n01000001 -> 65  -> A\n01010100 -> 84  -> T\n01001000 -> 72  -> H\n01001001 -> 73  -> I\n01010011 -> 83  -> S\n01000110 -> 70  -> F\n01010101 -> 85  -> U\n01001110 -> 78  -> N\n\nThe original message is \"MATHISFUN\"."
